  "text": "Although WT myocytes survive the initial Ca 2þ overload, the strong activation of several pathways may overwhelm the cellular defence mechanisms in mdx cells. It has been postulated for many years that proteases are a downstream Ca 2þ -activated target involved in protein degradation and necrosis of dystrophic skeletal muscle. [CITATION_1] Calpain is considered to be a likely candidate, as its expression is greater in mdx muscle. [CITATION_2] Because calpain is expressed in heart, and because calpain inhibitors protect from ischaemia-reperfusion injury, [CITATION_3] it is likely that this protease forms a part of the cellular death pathway in mdx heart.",
